    {
      "name": "Socket.IO",
      "description": "Real-time WebSocket events via Socket.IO.\n\nURL: {{socketUrl}}  (no /api/v1 prefix — connects directly to the server root)\nNamespace: /  (default)\nTransport: Socket.IO (not plain WebSocket)\n\nAUTHENTICATION\nPass the JWT accessToken in the handshake auth object:\n  { auth: { token: '<accessToken>' } }\nThe gateway verifies it on connect and disconnects the socket if invalid or missing.\n\nROOMS\n  user:{userId}        — every authenticated user joins this room automatically on connect\n  driver:available     — drivers join this manually via driver:subscribe-jobs\n\nFLOW OVERVIEW\n  1. Connect with accessToken in handshake auth\n  2. Driver calls driver:subscribe-jobs to receive broadcast job offers\n  3. Driver emits driver:location every ~3-5 s while on an active job\n  4. Server forwards driver:location to the assigned customer in real time\n  5. Server emits job:new / job:direct-offer / job:status-update / notification as server-side events",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "── CLIENT → SERVER ──",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Connect (handshake)",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "Establish a Socket.IO connection.\n\nClient code example:\n  import { io } from 'socket.io-client';\n  const socket = io('{{socketUrl}}', {\n    auth: { token: '<accessToken>' },\n    transports: ['websocket'],\n  });\n\nOn success the socket is placed in room user:{userId}.\nOn failure (missing/invalid token) the server immediately disconnects the client."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "driver:subscribe-jobs",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "ROLE: DRIVER only\n\nJoins the driver:available room so the driver receives job:new broadcast events.\nCall this after connecting and whenever the driver goes online.\n\nEmit payload:\n  socket.emit('driver:subscribe-jobs', { radius: 20 });\n\nPayload fields:\n  radius  number  optional  Search radius in km (stored client-side; default 20)\n\nAcknowledgement (returned to caller):\n  { event: 'subscribed', data: { radius: 20 } }"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "driver:unsubscribe-jobs",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "ROLE: DRIVER only\n\nLeaves the driver:available room. The driver will no longer receive job:new events.\nCall this when the driver goes offline.\n\nEmit:\n  socket.emit('driver:unsubscribe-jobs');\n\nAcknowledgement:\n  { event: 'unsubscribed' }"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "driver:location",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "ROLE: DRIVER only\n\nSend the driver's live GPS position. Emit every 3-5 seconds while on an active job.\n\nEmit payload:\n  socket.emit('driver:location', {\n    lat:     40.7128,\n    lng:     -74.0060,\n    heading: 90,      // optional, degrees 0-360\n    speed:   60,      // optional, km/h\n  });\n\nPayload fields:\n  lat      number   required  Latitude\n  lng      number   required  Longitude\n  heading  number   optional  Bearing in degrees\n  speed    number   optional  Speed in km/h\n\nServer behaviour:\n  1. Looks up the driver's active job (status: BOOKED | ON_WAY | ARRIVED | LOADED | IN_TRANSIT)\n  2. Immediately forwards coordinates to user:{customerId} room as driver:location event\n  3. Throttled DB write — persists latest position to DriverProfile at most once per 5 seconds\n     (latitude, longitude, lastLocationAt)"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "── SERVER → CLIENT ──",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "job:new  [driver:available room]",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "Broadcast job available — emitted to ALL drivers in the driver:available room.\nTriggered when a customer creates a broadcast job.\n\nListen:\n  socket.on('job:new', (data) => { ... });\n\nPayload:\n  {\n    jobId:          string   // Job ID\n    truckType:      string   // e.g. 'Flatbed'\n    pickupAddress:  string\n    dropoffAddress: string\n    distanceKm:     number\n    estimatedFare:  number\n  }"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "job:direct-offer  [user:{driverId}]",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "Direct job offer — emitted to a specific driver's user:{driverId} room.\nTriggered when a customer creates a job with targetDriverId.\n\nListen:\n  socket.on('job:direct-offer', (data) => { ... });\n\nPayload:\n  {\n    jobId:          string\n    pickupAddress:  string\n    dropoffAddress: string\n    estimatedFare:  number\n    timeoutSeconds: number   // offer expiry window\n  }"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "job:status-update  [user:{customerId}]",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "Job status changed — emitted to the customer's user:{customerId} room.\nTriggered whenever a driver advances the job status (accept, ON_WAY, ARRIVED, etc.).\n\nListen:\n  socket.on('job:status-update', (data) => { ... });\n\nPayload:\n  {\n    jobId:  string\n    status: 'BOOKED' | 'ON_WAY' | 'ARRIVED' | 'LOADED' | 'IN_TRANSIT' | 'DELIVERED' | 'CANCELLED'\n  }"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "driver:location  [user:{customerId}]",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "Real-time driver GPS forwarded to the assigned customer.\nEmitted immediately (not throttled) every time the driver sends driver:location.\nOnly emitted while the job is in an active status (BOOKED | ON_WAY | ARRIVED | LOADED | IN_TRANSIT).\n\nListen:\n  socket.on('driver:location', (data) => { ... });\n\nPayload:\n  {\n    jobId:   string\n    lat:     number\n    lng:     number\n    heading: number | undefined\n    speed:   number | undefined\n    ts:      number   // Unix ms timestamp\n  }"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "notification  [user:{userId}]",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{socketUrl}}", "host": ["{{socketUrl}}"] },
                "description": "In-app notification pushed to a specific user's user:{userId} room.\nEmitted whenever NotificationService.create() is called (job events, system alerts, etc.).\n\nListen:\n  socket.on('notification', (data) => { ... });\n\nPayload:\n  {\n    id:        string\n    type:      string   // e.g. JOB_ACCEPTED, PAYMENT_RECEIVED\n    title:     string\n    message:   string\n    data:      object   // extra context (jobId, amount, etc.)\n    createdAt: string   // ISO timestamp\n  }"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
